The paper focuses on end-to-end dialogue modeling and agent learning, which is a common topic in the field of natural language processing and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel multi-task representation learning method, which involves learning low-dimensional embeddings from data, and this is related to machine learning and deep learning, which are covered in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SD (Software Engineering and Programming). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on a public dataset, which involves information retrieval and search, and this is related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
